oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Aerial view of Chickamauga Dam
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Aerial view of the Chickamauga Dam.

The Chickamauga Dam, built in the 1930's, is a hydroelectric dam on the Tennessee River in Chattanooga owned by the Tennessee Valley Authority. The dam was constructed as part of a New Deal initiative for the purpose of providing flood control and economic development in the area during that time.
